Overview

This document outlines the integration plan for enchaining the functionality of our current Rhapsody system by leveraging the robust payments infrastructure of Chewy. The primary objective is to equip Rhapsody with comprehensive payment and ordering capabilities with Chewy.com inventory. Rhapsody will not store any personally identifiable financial information, and instead rely on the mature systems already in use by Chewy.com.

Goals

The goal of this design is to identify all of the internal services, their APIs, and specific inputs for each API that will be used in the Rhapsody system in order to enable checkouts with Chewy.com inventory.

Dependencies

  • Kyrios: Provides Chewy.com specific customer data, including ID and address information that is required to perform Chewy.com checkouts

  • Payments service: Core payment provider responsible for managing all transactions and payment information for Chewy.com orders. Rhapsody will utilize the payment service to retrieve necessary payment information from a customer’s Chewy.com account

  • Checkout service: Facilitates the execution of Chewy.com orders. Provides a cartless checkout process that Rhapsody will use to place Chewy.com orders.

    • Checkout service also owns Cart-B APIs, which we plan to use to add items to customer carts during payment failure use cases.

  • OMS: Order management system that provides comprehensive order information. Rhapsody will query individual orders post-payment to provide customers will details about their order.

Assumptions

  • All payment information and processing will be handled by existing Chewy services. Rhapsody will not store or process any customer financial information.

  • Checkout cartless APIs will support placing autoship orders (pending prioritization by checkout team)

  • Kyrios, Payments-B, Checkout-B, Cart-B, OMS APIs are all accessible with S2S auth.

  • Rhapsody will have a dedicated business channel from OMS/EDW team

Risks

  • Cart-B APIs are not accessible via S2S auth at the moment. Rhapsody needs Cart-B access to add items to customer carts during payment failure use cases. Checkout team currently does not have this work prioritized.

Sequence Diagrams

Happy path - Chewy order placed within Rhapsody

  • Use cases:

    • Happy path

    • Place order with only autoship items

    • Place order with some autoship items

    • Payment not found path

    • Address not found path

    • Payment declined on checkout path

    • Payment declined after checkout completed path

    • Item price changed path

    • Happy path add items to customers chewy cart

    • Add items to cart failure

    • Happy path pay with gift card balance only (still requires additional paymentId)

    • Happy path pay with gift card balance + additional payment

    • Gift card balance not sufficient and additional payment not valid

    • Get order details - happy path

    • Order details not found

Payments-B

Description: GET payment methods stored in customer wallet
Base url: https://payments-b-{region}.opta.{env}.aws.chewy.cloud/api/v1
Endpoint: /customers/{customer-id}/{wallet-id}/payment-methods

Request:

Attributes

Data Type

Required

Notes

customer-id

string

TRUE

  • Kyrios id

wallet-id

string

TRUE

  • Wallet-Id can be defaulted with keyword "primary" when wallet-id is unknown to perform transaction against the primary wallet.

  • Rhapsody will always use ‘primary’ as wallet-id

  • Primary wallet is the default wallet where chewy.com payment methods are stored

x-request-id

string

TRUE

  • UUID from Rhapsody for tracing purposes. Can be any value we decide

type

string

FALSE

  • Example values we can filter down to: CREDITCARD, PAYPAL, ACCOUNTBALANCE

exclude

array[string]

FALSE

  • Specify list of fields to be excluded from response

Response attributes needed for Rhapsody workflows:

 

Notes:

  • Payments team creates the “primary” wallet whenever a payment method is created for chewy.com orders.

  • If the customer does not have a “primary” wallet, API will return an empty response with 200 code.

  • Payment-methods are already filtered down to only ACTIVE payments. GOOGLEPAY and APPLEPAY methods are also filtered out.

Required Body fields

Description

cartless

Order object

cartless.caller

Business channel. Can be any value we choose. Proposed business channel value: RHAPSODY

cartless id

  • String id of the order. If not passed, checkout team will generate one for us.

  • Can be any id we decide on. Useful for tracing our checkout request in Checkout logs.

  • Sent to Promotion API Service

cartless items

List of item objects for purchase

cartless items id

  • String Id of an item.

  • Can be any id we decide on. Should be some unique id.

cartless items partNumber

Part number of the item in Chewy services.

cartless items quantity

Integer for how many of an item to purchase

cartless shipment

Shipment object to contain the address and other fields

cartless shipment addressId

String id of a mailing address. AddressID retrieved as default address (if set) from Kyrios-B

cartless shipment address id

Same as addressId above.

cartless promotions (confirmed not required)

List of promotions used during purchase.

Gift card balance usage:

  • Gift card balances on an account are represented as ACCOUNTBALANCE

  • In order to use ACCOUNTBALANCE as a payment method, we need to pass in a secondary payment method along with it*

* Technically we can pass in just ACCOUNTBALANCE payment method if the total charge is less than the balance, but this may be changing in the future. Thus for Rhapsody use case, we should always pass in a second payment method when using ACCOUNTBALANCE
